cs.NE, cs.DS, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SY

This paper deals with stochastic global optimization algorithms, which are commonly used in the field of machine learning and optimization. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also involves the use of probability theory and formal structures, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper discusses the convergence of algorithms, which could place it in the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.SY (Systems and Control).
